Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.99,0:00:37.02,English,,0,0,0,,This is a quote from the {\i1}Futurist Manifesto{\i0} written by Italian poet, Filippo Tommaso Marinetti,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.48,0:00:39.05,English,,0,0,0,,and published in 1909.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.40,0:00:43.12,English,,0,0,0,,With his work, he and his cohort announced to the world a new movement...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.12,0:00:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,that fetishized industrial progress and man's triumph over nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:53.14,English,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that the world had entered into a new age of unprecedented technological innovation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.44,0:00:56.79,English,,0,0,0,,they unabashedly declared that Humanity should free itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.10,0:01:01.12,English,,0,0,0,,from the shackles of the traditions, tastes and morals of the past...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.12,0:01:03.47,English,,0,0,0,,in pursuit of, well, the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.82,0:01:06.60,English,,0,0,0,,Progress to them should come at any expense,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.99,0:01:08.35,English,,0,0,0,,even that of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.72,0:01:10.76,English,,0,0,0,,In addition to valorizing war and violence,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.09,0:01:15.00,English,,0,0,0,,the core Italian futurists were also ardent nationalists,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.39,0:01:19.85,English,,0,0,0,,seeing this movement as Italy’s opportunity to reassert itself onto the world stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.99,0:01:22.85,English,,0,0,0,,instead of acting as a sort of nursing home for antiquity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.24,0:01:26.49,English,,0,0,0,,Oh and they also hated feminism and women broadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.78,0:01:29.05,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, so it should come to no surprise then that...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.05,0:01:33.57,English,,0,0,0,,many of these Italian futurists became Fascists in the coming decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.94,0:01:35.21,English,,0,0,0,,But back to the quote,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.74,0:01:38.42,English,,0,0,0,,the futurists weren't just to let the past die sort of group,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.80,0:01:40.77,English,,0,0,0,,they wanted to kill the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.80,0:01:46.08,English,,0,0,0,,literally demolishing museums and libraries was a core tenet of their manifesto.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.49,0:01:49.70,English,,0,0,0,,And while the proper futurist movement peaked back in the 20s and 30s,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.95,0:01:54.33,English,,0,0,0,,you can still find elements of their philosophy permitting throughout our culture today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.71,0:01:59.65,English,,0,0,0,,Specifically, this one core theme, this reckless contempt for what came before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:02.59,English,,0,0,0,,It's something that hasn't completely gone away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:09.48,English,,0,0,0,,And I see that theme popping up time and time again, and, to be frank, it troubles me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.13,0:02:22.46,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it's just me, but the last few years of the internet have felt pretty stagnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.81,0:02:24.67,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's nostalgia goggles kicking in,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.67,0:02:29.32,English,,0,0,0,,but I feel like the current internet climate feels much less optimistic and exciting...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.60,0:02:31.84,English,,0,0,0,,compared to the 2000s and the 2010s.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:35.48,English,,0,0,0,,Back then, we saw an explosion of new web-based services and products...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.58,0:02:38.01,English,,0,0,0,,that were redefining entire industries.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.24,0:02:41.94,English,,0,0,0,,Everything from managing sales funnels to doing taxes to watching movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:43.78,English,,0,0,0,,The sky was the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.19,0:02:46.72,English,,0,0,0,,But now, markets have become saturated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:51.33,English,,0,0,0,,The competitive fronts between different companies have become increasingly entrenched.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.76,0:02:55.46,English,,0,0,0,,And so in pursuit of continuously increasing profits,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.77,0:02:58.74,English,,0,0,0,,companies have turned to squeezing more money from the end user.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.98,0:03:03.03,English,,0,0,0,,While the industry as a whole desperately searches for its next iPhone moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.43,0:03:07.25,English,,0,0,0,,many companies and investors thought they were onto something with the metaverse or,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:11.31,English,,0,0,0,,putting block chain technology into everything for absolutely no fucking reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:13.76,English,,0,0,0,,or whatever other buzzword was being thrown around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.16,0:03:16.57,English,,0,0,0,,For a bit, it seemed like the emperor had no clothes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:20.70,English,,0,0,0,,but it looks like the bubble has finally popped on that Silicon Valley dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:25.20,English,,0,0,0,,And now the industry has looked to AI as the next major frontier for tech.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.46,0:03:29.17,English,,0,0,0,,But as impressive as generative chat bots like ChatGPT can be,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.37,0:03:32.27,English,,0,0,0,,AI isn't the Saving Grace for the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.45,0:03:35.65,English,,0,0,0,,And in a lot of ways, its novelty is distracting us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.91,0:03:40.96,English,,0,0,0,,from some really worrying trends that are making the Internet a far worse place to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.86,0:03:44.42,English,,0,0,0,,There isn't really an overarching thesis to this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.75,0:03:48.16,English,,0,0,0,,This is mostly just a collection of stories that really bother me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:52.46,English,,0,0,0,,and seem to suggest that the internet is headed for a far less interconnected future,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.82,0:03:54.88,English,,0,0,0,,where all websites become walled gardens,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.24,0:03:58.13,English,,0,0,0,,where every last time is squeezed out of each individual user,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:03:59.85,English,,0,0,0,,and where the internet as a whole,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.49,English,,0,0,0,,it was less useful and less usable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:08.98,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, Twitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:10.87,English,,0,0,0,,Oooh boy Twitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:15.62,English,,0,0,0,,What a ride has been ever since Elon Musk took the company's reigns back in October.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.95,0:04:19.92,English,,0,0,0,,It's been nothing but questionable decision after questionable decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.19,0:04:23.12,English,,0,0,0,,I cannot tell you how many times I've had rewrite this script,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:26.90,English,,0,0,0,,because of some new batshit insane thing that Twitter decided to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:31.85,English,,0,0,0,,Twitter’s advertising revenue in the US is down 59% compared to last year,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.16,0:04:34.29,English,,0,0,0,,following a mass exodus of advertisers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:38.06,English,,0,0,0,,And Twitter Blue has only been able to scrounge back $11,000,000...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.26,0:04:42.21,English,,0,0,0,,of the hundreds of millions of dollars the company potentially lost in revenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.71,0:04:44.91,English,,0,0,0,,And that number is probably pretty outdated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.27,0:04:49.37,English,,0,0,0,,A newer data has shown that more than half of Twitter Blue’s earliest subscribers...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.37,0:04:51.50,English,,0,0,0,,are no longer subscribed to the service.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:54.55,English,,0,0,0,,Musk has made it clear that he wants to transform Twitter...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.74,0:04:57.71,English,,0,0,0,,into X, an omnipotent super app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.99,0:05:01.04,English,,0,0,0,,You're all in one place for communication, finances,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.17,0:05:03.84,English,,0,0,0,,and media consumption that can dip to WeChat in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.50,0:05:07.47,English,,0,0,0,,And we've seen Twitter go full steam ahead into transforming itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.88,0:05:09.71,English,,0,0,0,,Twitter Inc. has been renamed X Corp.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.98,0:05:13.94,English,,0,0,0,,Musk has announced that more robust DMs and video calls will be eventually coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.26,0:05:17.79,English,,0,0,0,,And users can now trade stocks on Twitter in a partnership with Etoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.04,0:05:21.50,English,,0,0,0,,I think the most significant Italian change...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:26.00,English,,0,0,0,,that Twitter has implemented so far revolves around access to its API
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.45,0:05:27.59,English,,0,0,0,,For those of you who don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:30.55,English,,0,0,0,,API stands for “application programming interface”,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.90,0:05:35.53,English,,0,0,0,,and it's the protocol that's used to communicate between different computer programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:39.75,English,,0,0,0,,So if you need to push data or send a command from one system to another,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.53,English,,0,0,0,,anything from Google Sheets, Salesforce to Stripe,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.78,0:05:44.42,English,,0,0,0,,you would use an API for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.64,0:05:46.86,English,,0,0,0,,API are pretty ubiquitous throughout the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.18,0:05:49.01,English,,0,0,0,,For consumer grade online services,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.05,0:05:52.69,English,,0,0,0,,it's pretty rare that access to the API is put behind a paywall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.16,0:05:55.45,English,,0,0,0,,And this is especially the case for social media,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:05:58.88,English,,0,0,0,,but back in February of this year, Twitter did just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:01.36,English,,0,0,0,,Developers and researchers were stunned to discover...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.48,English,,0,0,0,,that they would have to start paying to access Twitter's API.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:08.46,English,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of accounts announced that they were shutting down all because of this change,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.62,0:06:11.29,English,,0,0,0,,from the national weather service, sending out weather updates,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.31,0:06:14.60,English,,0,0,0,,to local transportation authorities, sending out transportation updates,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.90,0:06:16.89,English,,0,0,0,,and of course, fun gimmick accounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.48,0:06:20.09,English,,0,0,0,,Musk claim that the reason for this was to limit bot spam,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.12,0:06:21.66,English,,0,0,0,,but developers have claimed that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.89,0:06:25.13,English,,0,0,0,,the real spam comes from scripts injected into Twitter as web client,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.56,0:06:27.14,English,,0,0,0,,or from stolen API keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.68,0:06:31.10,English,,0,0,0,,And while some of the original API plans have been walked back like...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.48,0:06:35.21,English,,0,0,0,,through the reintroduction of a free tier albeit, an extremely limited one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:39.28,English,,0,0,0,,This is, in addition to removing API access to third party clients,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.59,0:06:44.99,English,,0,0,0,,a clear signal that the future of Twitter will be more and more hostile to its developer community...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.29,0:06:48.34,English,,0,0,0,,and that it wants to become a walled garden for the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.73,0:06:50.90,English,,0,0,0,,Also, something really funny that I found is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.09,0:06:54.08,English,,0,0,0,,in order to request access to Twitter enterprise API,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.62,0:06:56.18,English,,0,0,0,,you have to fill out a fucking Google form.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.42,0:06:57.61,English,,0,0,0,,It sends you to a Google form.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.61,0:07:02.89,English,,0,0,0,,People who are gonna be paying $42,000 a month are sent to a Google form!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.89,0:07:03.65,English,,0,0,0,,It's so funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.32,0:07:06.87,English,,0,0,0,,In the wake of this change, we've seen Reddit, follow suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:09.88,English,,0,0,0,,Reddit will begin charging for access to its API,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.13,0:07:13.31,English,,0,0,0,,pricing out many developers who manage third party clients with the site,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:17.82,English,,0,0,0,,even the ones that offer tools to help communities manage and moderate themselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.99,0:07:20.86,English,,0,0,0,,that Reddit flatly does not offer out of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:23.06,English,,0,0,0,,Reddit’s reasoning for this is twofold.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.26,0:07:26.06,English,,0,0,0,,For one, it is rightly identified that there is a lot of useful,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.33,0:07:28.33,English,,0,0,0,,easily accessible information on the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.73,0:07:31.42,English,,0,0,0,,I mean how many times have you gone to search something on Google...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.71,0:07:33.81,English,,0,0,0,,and appended Reddit to the end of your query?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.18,0:07:36.56,English,,0,0,0,,Which is something we're gonna discuss later, by the way, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.98,0:07:40.75,English,,0,0,0,,Because of this, Reddit is hoping to protect itself from data scraping.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.06,0:07:43.49,English,,0,0,0,,OpenAI previously revealed that Reddit was indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:46.08,English,,0,0,0,,one of the sources used to train its AI models.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.41,0:07:49.66,English,,0,0,0,,And Reddit doesn't want that to happen again without getting a cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.36,0:07:53.63,English,,0,0,0,,Also, as Reddit continues to put around the idea of going public,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:56.87,English,,0,0,0,,it wants to find new ways to monetize itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.30,0:07:59.09,English,,0,0,0,,In case, it's not obvious,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.09,0:08:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,all of this not only makes things worse for developers, but, also for users,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.39,0:08:04.94,English,,0,0,0,,it limits what can be done on these sites...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.97,0:08:09.13,English,,0,0,0,,and advances the idea that there can and should only be one way,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:12.95,English,,0,0,0,,one set of approved channels for a user to interact with the site.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.42,0:08:18.56,English,,0,0,0,,It makes these sites less useful by eliminating automated accounts that supply good information.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.84,0:08:22.88,English,,0,0,0,,It limits the data that you can get about your own and other's Internet presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.17,0:08:26.76,English,,0,0,0,,It limits the research that can be done on these sites and on their communities.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.22,0:08:30.53,English,,0,0,0,,And it flat out limits human creativity by restricting developers...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.56,0:08:33.97,English,,0,0,0,,from creating different and unique user experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:41.47,English,,0,0,0,,Back in May of this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.51,0:08:45.13,English,,0,0,0,,Google announced that it will be deleting inactive Google accounts on mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.48,0:08:49.17,English,,0,0,0,,Specifically, those that haven't seen any activity in 2 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.68,0:08:52.80,English,,0,0,0,,Countless emails, attachments, Google drive files, photos, and more,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.08,0:08:56.28,English,,0,0,0,,will be deleted at the end of this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.61,0:09:00.50,English,,0,0,0,,And what struck me the most was just how poorly this change was announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.83,0:09:03.58,English,,0,0,0,,It was just casually dropped in a security blog post.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.90,0:09:07.60,English,,0,0,0,,And the lack of detail had people speculating as to whether this would mean that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.67,0:09:12.09,English,,0,0,0,,entire channels on YouTube would be removed if the associated Google account hadn't been active.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.44,0:09:16.34,English,,0,0,0,,The fact that they only updated the blog post after this backlash just shows that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:19.49,English,,0,0,0,,they really didn't care enough to think about this the first go-round,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:22.97,English,,0,0,0,,or maybe that they were actually thinking about deleting YouTube videos at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:27.68,English,,0,0,0,,But God, even after they clarify these changes, things still look pretty bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.20,0:09:30.25,English,,0,0,0,,Imagine you have a dead family member...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:32.85,English,,0,0,0,,and you didn't know how to recover their account until it was too late,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.31,0:09:37.40,English,,0,0,0,,or I don't know you were in a coma, or God forbid, you were imprisoned for whatever reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.70,0:09:42.50,English,,0,0,0,,Imagine your Google account, the crux of your online identity being erased in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.77,0:09:44.24,English,,0,0,0,,Poof! Gone forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:47.68,English,,0,0,0,,You have to start from scratch and also fight an uphill battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.94,0:09:50.04,English,,0,0,0,,proving that you are who you say you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:53.10,English,,0,0,0,,Twitter has also announced that they'll be doing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.20,0:09:55.58,English,,0,0,0,,They would begin purging inactive accounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.94,0:09:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,Whereas Google at least had the courtesy to say that it was for security reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.64,0:10:03.75,English,,0,0,0,,it seems like Twitter is literally just trying to trim off as much fat as they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:07.17,English,,0,0,0,,Their official policy states that an account risks deletion...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.40,0:10:10.75,English,,0,0,0,,if it's inactive for 30 days, a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.07,0:10:13.79,English,,0,0,0,,Imgur also decided recently that a bunch of old photos...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:16.93,English,,0,0,0,,and forum content just wasn't worth keeping around anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.09,0:10:21.12,English,,0,0,0,,Despite these forums being the original reason, Imgur got popular in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:26.44,English,,0,0,0,,All the while, streaming services like Disney+, HBO Max — now dubbed, just a Max,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:31.64,English,,0,0,0,,Hulu and Showtime, have removed access to dozens and dozens of movies and TV shows,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:34.72,English,,0,0,0,,and it's not just content that they've licensed from other companies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.87,0:10:37.98,English,,0,0,0,,It also includes movies and shows produced in-house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.24,0:10:41.68,English,,0,0,0,,By limiting their libraries to current or uber popular content,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:45.69,English,,0,0,0,,these companies can take advantage of certain tax breaks in some cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.96,0:10:51.28,English,,0,0,0,,or eliminate the costs of licensing fees or residuals that they pay out to the contents creators.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:54.90,English,,0,0,0,,Literally less than 6 months after wrapping up its first season,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.15,0:10:58.42,English,,0,0,0,,the Disney+ fantasy series {\i1}Willow{\i0} was pulled from streaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.80,0:11:00.08,English,,0,0,0,,That's just crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.08,0:11:02.56,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, everyone complains about the content mill,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.61,0:11:05.95,English,,0,0,0,,but it's just so unbelievably cruel to see a piece of art...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.22,0:11:09.17,English,,0,0,0,,that people have spent years of their lives working on,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.49,0:11:11.53,English,,0,0,0,,being tossed away like it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.03,0:11:16.19,English,,0,0,0,,All this while there's a writer strike going on behind you to add insult to injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.62,0:11:18.46,English,,0,0,0,,This also means that in many cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.46,0:11:21.71,English,,0,0,0,,there's no longer a legal means of watching this content.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:25.03,English,,0,0,0,,While these sites are deleting content of their own volition,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:28.39,English,,0,0,0,,other organizations are being forced to remove content from the web.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.80,0:11:30.85,English,,0,0,0,,Another pillar of the Internet, the Internet Archive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.89,0:11:33.37,English,,0,0,0,,was dealt a major blow in the lawsuit back in March.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.54,0:11:36.99,English,,0,0,0,,Book publishers argued that there was no legal basis for the Internet Archive...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.99,0:11:40.20,English,,0,0,0,,to lend out digital books, even through controlled digital lending.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.44,0:11:41.83,English,,0,0,0,,And the courts agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.09,0:11:43.75,English,,0,0,0,,while the Internet Archive is appealing,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:51.31,English,,0,0,0,,it's still so tragic to think that such a wealth of knowledge could be rendered, utterly useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:52.69,English,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm not a lawyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.69,0:11:55.66,English,,0,0,0,,so I can't speak to the particulars of the case with any authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.66,0:12:00.30,English,,0,0,0,,but boy, does it feel like publishers would outlaw brick and mortar libraries if they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.75,0:12:04.73,English,,0,0,0,,Free and open access to information is at the core of the Internet ethos,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.73,0:12:09.59,English,,0,0,0,,and well it's just so sad to see so much of that information going up in smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.77,0:12:12.34,English,,0,0,0,,Companies only see value in data that makes the money,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.58,0:12:17.89,English,,0,0,0,,and so these accounts and their associated data are designated as digital access.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:21.28,English,,0,0,0,,If anything, these actions by major online platforms...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.64,0:12:23.96,English,,0,0,0,,highlight the fragility of our digital experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.25,0:12:27.82,English,,0,0,0,,and serve as a reminder of the unfortunate impermanence
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.98,0:12:31.03,English,,0,0,0,,of the information we create and consume daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.48,0:12:40.85,English,,0,0,0,,The state of online search right now is pretty disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.27,0:12:43.40,English,,0,0,0,,If you innocently type something into Google,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:45.98,English,,0,0,0,,Google then blasts you with a deluge of ads,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:48.84,English,,0,0,0,,carousels, and widgets that it thinks you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:51.55,English,,0,0,0,,And then once you get to the organic search results,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.55,0:12:54.33,English,,0,0,0,,it's filled to the brim with generic solace,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.45,0:12:57.19,English,,0,0,0,,keyword written listings that more often than not,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.45,0:12:59.16,English,,0,0,0,,frankly don't answer your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.65,0:13:02.62,English,,0,0,0,,It's quite the development that in the world of online search,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.79,0:13:06.41,English,,0,0,0,,the burden of curation has shifted back to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:10.10,English,,0,0,0,,This is all due to the ubiquity of search engine optimization,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.36,0:13:13.74,English,,0,0,0,,or SEO, the process of formatting and writing web content ways...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.89,0:13:16.91,English,,0,0,0,,that appeal to search engine crawlers and algorithms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:19.99,English,,0,0,0,,SEO however, is less straightforward than it sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:24.38,English,,0,0,0,,In reality, search engine optimization, as a field is constantly changing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.60,0:13:28.78,English,,0,0,0,,feeds off of infrequent and ambiguous hints that Google reveals about its algorithm,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.16,0:13:31.05,English,,0,0,0,,requires ample trial and error.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:35.25,English,,0,0,0,,As you may have guessed, is fraught with ostensibly know-it-all gurus
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.38,0:13:37.03,English,,0,0,0,,and a hefty dose of snake oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.43,0:13:42.31,English,,0,0,0,,I'm not alone for my contempt for how SEO practices have sterilized and homogenized the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.84,0:13:45.61,English,,0,0,0,,However, in many ways, it's a monster of Google own making.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.99,0:13:47.12,English,,0,0,0,,As one writer puts it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.19,0:13:49.77,English,,0,0,0,,Google has been playing an endless game of whack-a-mole...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.77,0:13:53.17,English,,0,0,0,,trying to combat SEO marketers from abusing Google's algorithm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.37,0:13:57.84,English,,0,0,0,,for their own benefit by giving their sites all the trappings of authoritative content.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:02.09,English,,0,0,0,,And naturally with more traffic, you're able to make more money by serving ads or,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.31,0:14:05.83,English,,0,0,0,,by funneling users into using your product or service.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.11,0:14:08.04,English,,0,0,0,,And even on sites with useful content,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.04,0:14:11.97,English,,0,0,0,,you oftentimes have to scroll through a whole dissertation to find what you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:15.20,English,,0,0,0,,because many sites cater to the tastes of Google algorithm
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.39,0:14:18.62,English,,0,0,0,,and not the end user trying to find answers on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.14,0:14:20.11,English,,0,0,0,,Frequently sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.48,0:14:22.42,English,,0,0,0,,Like I said before, more often than not,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.42,0:14:26.77,English,,0,0,0,,you're more likely to find what you're looking for by a pending Reddit to the end of your query...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.77,0:14:28.14,English,,0,0,0,,and then digging through forums.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.67,0:14:32.97,English,,0,0,0,,Alternatively, many youngsters have started using TikTok as a search engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.13,0:14:36.41,English,,0,0,0,,seeking more authentic and personal sources of information that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.79,0:14:40.00,English,,0,0,0,,Even Google has admitted that around 40% of Gen-Zers...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.28,0:14:44.54,English,,0,0,0,,go to TikTok or Instagram instead of Google for certain search queries.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.84,0:14:47.11,English,,0,0,0,,And it's not just the results are less helpful,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.39,0:14:50.11,English,,0,0,0,,there are also dangerous implications for Internet history,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:52.58,English,,0,0,0,,In the pursuit of hosting evergreen content —
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.81,0:14:55.50,English,,0,0,0,,content that will reliably attract an audience long term,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.86,0:14:58.59,English,,0,0,0,,articles and blog posts are constantly rewritten.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.07,0:15:02.24,English,,0,0,0,,New hyperlinks, better headings, better headlines, better copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:06.95,English,,0,0,0,,This is all done to make the content more marketable and to continue to drive users to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.09,0:15:12.13,English,,0,0,0,,However, there's something sad about history being rewritten with little to no disclosure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.31,0:15:17.62,English,,0,0,0,,Web publishers also frequently prune content on their sites that is out of date or not in vogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.83,0:15:20.23,English,,0,0,0,,As another writer puts it this all results in...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:23.76,English,,0,0,0,,an Internet with no institutional memory or accountability.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.88,0:15:25.44,English,,0,0,0,,So when Google and Bing announced that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:29.24,English,,0,0,0,,generative AI responses will be taking center stage in search going forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.53,0:15:32.15,English,,0,0,0,,some people hailed this as an incredible development,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:36.64,English,,0,0,0,,hoping that would actually give users the answers that they are looking for more quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.79,0:15:41.32,English,,0,0,0,,Others have held it as the death of SEO as these generative AI responses,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.32,0:15:43.72,English,,0,0,0,,while they cite where they get their information from,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:47.10,English,,0,0,0,,will kill off a good chunk of organic search traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:51.94,English,,0,0,0,,And from the looks of things, it looks like generative AI responses in search...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.47,0:15:56.42,English,,0,0,0,,just flat out sucks and causes more problems than it solves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.86,0:15:59.78,English,,0,0,0,,It flat out plagiarize some responses and the parts...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.80,0:16:02.29,English,,0,0,0,,that doesn't play to rise are often just wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:06.75,English,,0,0,0,,because it just strings words together that it thinks are likely to appear next to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.01,0:16:10.34,English,,0,0,0,,In order for it to deliver the quality of user experience people expect,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.64,0:16:13.61,English,,0,0,0,,it would be better sometimes just for to flat out plagiarize.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.91,0:16:15.10,English,,0,0,0,,But that comes at the cost of...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.10,0:16:18.88,English,,0,0,0,,screwing over the people who made the information available in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.11,0:16:23.78,English,,0,0,0,,Also, since its scraping sites that are often written to be optimized for search,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.14,0:16:26.35,English,,0,0,0,,I expect that we'll see plenty of situations...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.60,0:16:28.84,English,,0,0,0,,where it's just gonna be garbage in, garbage out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:31.29,English,,0,0,0,,I mean there are situations where users themselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.32,0:16:33.62,English,,0,0,0,,can't even find the information that they're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.80,0:16:36.50,English,,0,0,0,,And Google/Bing’s generative AI models...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.66,0:16:40.43,English,,0,0,0,,are gonna be looking at the exact same web pages that the users are going through.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.77,0:16:44.04,English,,0,0,0,,So I sincerely doubt that these generative responses...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.28,0:16:46.20,English,,0,0,0,,will be able to do what users can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.70,0:16:47.98,English,,0,0,0,,And to make matters worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.17,0:16:51.03,English,,0,0,0,,Google and Bing have both announced that they'll be placing ads...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.03,0:16:52.72,English,,0,0,0,,into their generative search responses,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:56.87,English,,0,0,0,,meaning that even when these generative responses turn out to be useful,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.17,0:16:58.25,English,,0,0,0,,they'll be riddled with ads,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.47,0:17:00.48,English,,0,0,0,,making the user experience all the more tedious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.99,0:17:05.65,English,,0,0,0,,Google and Bing are putting more junk in between the user and the information they're looking for...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:11.31,English,,0,0,0,,and essentially are punishing sites that have good information for having good information.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.49,0:17:12.48,English,,0,0,0,,As far as I can tell,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.48,0:17:14.89,English,,0,0,0,,when these models have good information to work with,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:16.96,English,,0,0,0,,they can do some pretty amazing things,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:20.60,English,,0,0,0,,but that's just not how the Internet exists right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.87,0:17:24.01,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a technical problem that can be solved over time, but,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.40,0:17:27.60,English,,0,0,0,,nonetheless, it's still pretty shameful and condescending for companies...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:30.37,English,,0,0,0,,to push something so broken onto the masses so quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:33.52,English,,0,0,0,,and to greatly over promise on its capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.71,0:17:35.74,English,,0,0,0,,Back when search engines first came out of the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.98,0:17:37.91,English,,0,0,0,,they solved a very specific problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.15,0:17:41.05,English,,0,0,0,,and made all corners of the Internet accessible in one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.48,0:17:45.87,English,,0,0,0,,But today it feels like that most search engines have abandoned that commitment —
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:47.18,English,,0,0,0,,user-centricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:50.82,English,,0,0,0,,And while Google has been taking steps to provide search results...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.01,0:17:53.36,English,,0,0,0,,that connect users to real world experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.60,0:17:58.70,English,,0,0,0,,it's obvious that connecting users with this sort of content directly is not Google’s priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.18,0:18:01.26,English,,0,0,0,,Only through a commitment to user empowerment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.60,0:18:04.84,English,,0,0,0,,can we hope to restore the value and utility of online search...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.22,0:18:08.06,English,,0,0,0,,in an era dominated by algorithms and AI.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.71,0:18:15.91,English,,0,0,0,,Recently, some YouTube users have gotten notices that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.91,0:18:18.51,English,,0,0,0,,they'll be required to disable their AD block going forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.79,0:18:21.25,English,,0,0,0,,or otherwise opt into YouTube Premium.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.59,0:18:24.48,English,,0,0,0,,I'm a little surprised that they haven't done this a while ago but,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.84,0:18:28.93,English,,0,0,0,,yet again, we're at a crossroad where the user experience continues to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:34.35,English,,0,0,0,,But honestly, there's a more insidious and potentially harmful set of changes happening that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.52,0:18:37.05,English,,0,0,0,,I haven't really heard anyone discuss too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.43,0:18:42.06,English,,0,0,0,,That's Chrome transition to its Manifest V3 extension platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.24,0:18:45.94,English,,0,0,0,,A manifest file is one of the many files required in a Chrome extension...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.94,0:18:49.77,English,,0,0,0,,and defines the level of access to browser data and system resources...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.77,0:18:52.49,English,,0,0,0,,that it requires as well as its capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.60,0:18:57.08,English,,0,0,0,,Back in 2018, Google announced the beginning of their transition to Manifest V3,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.35,0:18:59.17,English,,0,0,0,,replacing Manifest V2.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.51,0:19:03.23,English,,0,0,0,,While the timeline of this transition has been delayed a handful of times,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.60,0:19:07.82,English,,0,0,0,,there are some serious consequences associated with these new specifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.26,0:19:12.44,English,,0,0,0,,The big one being that it will undermine the effectiveness of AD block extensions...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.51,0:19:15.28,English,,0,0,0,,and extensions that anonymous user information.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:19.97,English,,0,0,0,,While Google is asserting that these changes to the manifest are for the sake of privacy —
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.27,0:19:22.42,English,,0,0,0,,something that many developers dispute,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.47,0:19:27.14,English,,0,0,0,,it conveniently will also have the effect of having websites show more ads,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:30.54,English,,0,0,0,,which is what Google whole business model is based around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.98,0:19:34.15,English,,0,0,0,,The scariest part is that these changes won't be limited to just Chrome.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.36,0:19:38.72,English,,0,0,0,,They'll affect all Chromium-based browsers like Edge, Brave, Opera, and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.93,0:19:43.60,English,,0,0,0,,The only web browser of note that has pushed back against these changes is Firefox,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.96,0:19:48.53,English,,0,0,0,,saying that they'll continue to support web requests blocking features from Manifest V2,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.67,0:19:52.22,English,,0,0,0,,which are the foundation of anti-tracking extensions and AD blockers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.46,0:19:56.44,English,,0,0,0,,But that's what we get when one company essentially becomes the gatekeeper for...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:19:57.98,English,,0,0,0,,access to the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:19:59.27,English,,0,0,0,,Once they have that power,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:02.27,English,,0,0,0,,it's only a matter of time before they use it for their own benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.09,0:20:08.32,English,,0,0,0,,So like I said at the beginning of the video,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.65,0:20:12.08,English,,0,0,0,,a lot of futurists did become fascists later in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.42,0:20:14.70,English,,0,0,0,,However, that was not a universal rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.96,0:20:18.95,English,,0,0,0,,Futurism actually found a home on all sides of the political spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.24,0:20:24.41,English,,0,0,0,,That's because while some tenets of Marinetti’s Futurist Manifesto were reactionary,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.71,0:20:27.47,English,,0,0,0,,the core of the futurism project was not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.77,0:20:31.26,English,,0,0,0,,The one thing that I think the futurist movement deserves a lot of praise for...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.38,0:20:35.87,English,,0,0,0,,is that it brought into the mainstream, a new found optimism for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.01,0:20:39.99,English,,0,0,0,,They glorified technological advancement because they saw good in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.43,0:20:43.93,English,,0,0,0,,They celebrated human ingenuity as a freeing force.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.05,0:20:45.67,English,,0,0,0,,Over 100 years later, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.86,0:20:50.40,English,,0,0,0,,I struggle to find that sense of optimism, at least regards the modern Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:53.79,English,,0,0,0,,It seems like there's a roadblock on every road to progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.97,0:20:57.86,English,,0,0,0,,Or any progress that's been made on the Internet is being ratcheted backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.07,0:21:02.43,English,,0,0,0,,When corporations put the onus of their growth onto the shoulders of its users,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.75,0:21:04.15,English,,0,0,0,,nothing good can come of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.50,0:21:08.19,English,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, that's what we're seeing more and more of lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:10.35,English,,0,0,0,,While doing research for this video,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:15.11,English,,0,0,0,,I came across one article that I think perfectly encapsulates where we're headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.68,0:21:18.01,English,,0,0,0,,"We are living through the end of the useful Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:22.47,English,,0,0,0,,The future is informed discussion behind locked doors in discord and private fora.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:26.18,English,,0,0,0,,With the public facing web increasingly filled with detritus...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.42,0:21:31.03,English,,0,0,0,,generated by LLMs bearing only a stylistic resemblance to useful information,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.30,0:21:34.20,English,,0,0,0,,finding unbiased and independent product reviews,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.46,0:21:37.51,English,,0,0,0,,expert tech support and all manner of helpful advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.70,0:21:41.40,English,,0,0,0,,will now resemble the process by which one now searches for illegal sports streams
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.61,0:21:42.98,English,,0,0,0,,or pirated journal articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.41,0:21:47.14,English,,0,0,0,,The decades of real human conversation posted at places like Reddit...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:51.91,English,,0,0,0,,will prove useful training material for the mindless bots and deceptive marketers that replace it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.30,0:21:55.77,English,,0,0,0,,While the recent blackouts by several subreddits are certainly admirable,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.08,0:21:59.98,English,,0,0,0,,it doesn't change the fact that Reddit and all of the other companies I've talked about...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.26,0:22:02.43,English,,0,0,0,,have ownership of these platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.88,0:22:07.71,English,,0,0,0,,They are businesses who have a legal obligation to maximize their profit for their investors,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.91,0:22:11.48,English,,0,0,0,,and can make whatever changes they like, regardless of our own feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.05,0:22:15.52,English,,0,0,0,,But nonetheless, this would be the end of the Internet as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:20.43,English,,0,0,0,,Entire networks of people, incredibly passionate people across all sorts of sites...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.75,0:22:23.73,English,,0,0,0,,are at risk of breaking down or eroding away,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.11,0:22:25.88,English,,0,0,0,,or hiding in some shadowy corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.30,0:22:29.31,English,,0,0,0,,and that's just such a sad and unthinkable prospect.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.74,0:22:32.97,English,,0,0,0,,It's crucial to address these trends to ensure that the Internet...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.22,0:22:37.74,English,,0,0,0,,remains a vibrant and inclusive space for innovation and collaboration.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.20,0:22:39.77,English,,0,0,0,,By advocating for this openness,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:42.19,English,,0,0,0,,supporting developers and independent creators,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.49,0:22:43.89,English,,0,0,0,,and demanding transparency,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.26,0:22:47.72,English,,0,0,0,,we can hopefully work towards a more interconnected...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.03,0:22:52.14,English,,0,0,0,,and user-friendly Internet actually enriches our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.26,0:22:54.28,English,,0,0,0,,I've been 1C2.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.08,0:22:55.80,English,,0,0,0,,Thanks for watching.
Comment: 0,0:00:31.99,0:00:37.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这些文字引自意大利诗人菲利波·托马索·马里内蒂的 《未来主义宣言》
Comment: 0,0:00:37.48,0:00:39.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,发表于 1909 年
Comment: 0,0:00:39.40,0:00:43.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,通过他的作品   他和他的同伙向世界宣布了一个新的运动
Comment: 0,0:00:43.12,0:00:47.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,崇拜工业进步和人类对自然的胜利
Comment: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:53.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们认识到世界已经进入了一个前所未有的技术革新的新时代
Comment: 0,0:00:53.44,0:00:56.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,因此毫不掩饰地宣称
Comment: 0,0:00:57.10,0:01:01.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,人类应该摆脱过去的传统、品味和道德的束缚
Comment: 0,0:01:01.12,0:01:03.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,追求未来
Comment: 0,0:01:03.82,0:01:06.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,对他们来说   进步应该不惜一切代价
Comment: 0,0:01:06.99,0:01:08.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,哪怕是牺牲人的生命
Comment: 0,0:01:08.72,0:01:10.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,除了高度评价战争和暴力
Comment: 0,0:01:11.09,0:01:15.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,意大利的核心未来主义者也是热心的民族主义者
Comment: 0,0:01:15.39,0:01:19.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们将这场运动视为意大利在世界舞台上重新证明自己的机会
Comment: 0,0:01:19.99,0:01:22.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而不是充当某种古代的养老院
Comment: 0,0:01:23.24,0:01:26.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们还讨厌女性   憎恶女权
Comment: 0,0:01:26.78,0:01:29.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,所以说   许多意大利未来主义者在未来几十年里
Comment: 0,0:01:29.05,0:01:33.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,变成法西斯主义者   就不足为奇了
Comment: 0,0:01:33.94,0:01:35.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,回到引文
Comment: 0,0:01:35.74,0:01:38.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,未来主义者不仅仅想让过去像人类一样自然消亡
Comment: 0,0:01:38.80,0:01:40.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们想要扼杀过去
Comment: 0,0:01:40.80,0:01:46.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,摧毁博物馆和图书馆是他们宣言的核心原则
Comment: 0,0:01:46.49,0:01:49.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,虽然正派的未来主义者运动在二三十年代达到了顶峰
Comment: 0,0:01:49.95,0:01:54.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但你仍然可以发现他们的哲学元素渗透到我们今天的文化中
Comment: 0,0:01:54.71,0:01:59.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,特别是这个核心主题   这种对前人的不顾一切的蔑视
Comment: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:02.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它还没有完全消失
Comment: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:09.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我看到这个主题一次又一次地出现   坦率地说   这让我很烦恼
Comment: 0,0:02:18.13,0:02:22.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,不知道是否只有我在这么想   但互联网的最后几年感觉停滞不前
Comment: 0,0:02:22.81,0:02:24.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,也许是怀旧滤镜加成
Comment: 0,0:02:24.67,0:02:29.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但我觉得与 2000 年代和 2010 年代相比
Comment: 0,0:02:29.60,0:02:31.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,当前的互联网环境感觉不那么乐观和令人兴奋
Comment: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:35.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,那时   我们看到基于网络的新服务和产品的爆炸性增长
Comment: 0,0:02:35.58,0:02:38.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,重新定义了整个行业
Comment: 0,0:02:38.24,0:02:41.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,从管理销售渠道到纳税   再到看电影   无所不包
Comment: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:43.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,简直没有天花板
Comment: 0,0:02:44.19,0:02:46.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但现在市场已经饱和了
Comment: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:51.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,不同公司之间的竞争战线已经变得越来越稳固
Comment: 0,0:02:51.76,0:02:55.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,因此   为了追求不断增加的利润
Comment: 0,0:02:55.77,0:02:58.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,公司转向从终端用户那里榨取更多的钱
Comment: 0,0:02:58.98,0:03:03.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,当整个行业拼命寻找其下一个“重新定义”的时刻时
Comment: 0,0:03:03.43,0:03:07.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,许多公司和投资者认为他们在滥用元宇宙
Comment: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:11.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或将区块链技术融入一切玩意   就那啥毫无理由
Comment: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:13.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,反正用什么脏话来形容都一样
Comment: 0,0:03:14.16,0:03:16.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,有一段时间   科技公司还像没穿衣服的皇帝一样迷失于此
Comment: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:20.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但看起来   硅谷梦想的泡沫终于破灭了
Comment: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:25.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,现在   互联网行业将人工智能视作下一个科技前沿
Comment: 0,0:03:25.46,0:03:29.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但是   尽管像 ChatGPT 这样的生成式聊天机器人让人影响深刻
Comment: 0,0:03:29.37,0:03:32.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,人工智能并不是因特网的救星
Comment: 0,0:03:32.45,0:03:35.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,从很多方面讲   它的新奇反而在分散我们的注意力
Comment: 0,0:03:35.91,0:03:40.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,让我们忽视一些真正令人担忧的   让互联网变得更糟糕的趋势
Comment: 0,0:03:41.86,0:03:44.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,本视频没有一个总体论点
Comment: 0,0:03:44.75,0:03:48.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,主要是一组困扰我的故事
Comment: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:52.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它们表明互联网正走向一个远非互联的未来
Comment: 0,0:03:52.82,0:03:54.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,所有网站都变成有围墙的花园
Comment: 0,0:03:55.24,0:03:58.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,每个用户的每分每秒都被挤压出来
Comment: 0,0:03:58.49,0:03:59.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,互联网作为一个整体
Comment: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,其作用和可用性都降低了
Comment: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:08.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,噢   推特
Comment: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:10.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,来看看推特
Comment: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:15.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,自从埃隆·马斯克在十月夺回公司控制权以来   这段旅程真是美妙呵
Comment: 0,0:04:15.95,0:04:19.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,全是一个接着一个的令人质疑的决定
Comment: 0,0:04:20.19,0:04:23.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我的稿子不知道改了多少回
Comment: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:26.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,都跟不上推特做的屑事情
Comment: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:31.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在广告商大量外流后
Comment: 0,0:04:32.16,0:04:34.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,与去年相比   推特在美广告收入减少了 59%
Comment: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:38.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而推特蓝标会员只能从该公司可能损失的数亿美元中
Comment: 0,0:04:38.26,0:04:42.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,捡回 1100 万美元
Comment: 0,0:04:42.71,0:04:44.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而且这个数据很可能过时了
Comment: 0,0:04:45.27,0:04:49.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,一项较新的数据显示   最早开通蓝标会员的用户中
Comment: 0,0:04:49.37,0:04:51.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,一半以上都不再续订它了
Comment: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:54.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,马斯克明确表示他想要把推特转型
Comment: 0,0:04:54.74,0:04:57.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,转成“X” 一个全能的超级应用
Comment: 0,0:04:57.99,0:05:01.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,所有的沟通交流、财务
Comment: 0,0:05:01.17,0:05:03.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,和媒体消费都在一个应用   如同中国的微信
Comment: 0,0:05:04.50,0:05:07.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我们已经看到推特全力推进自我转型
Comment: 0,0:05:07.88,0:05:09.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,推特公司已更名为 X 公司
Comment: 0,0:05:09.98,0:05:13.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,马斯克宣布   推特会加入更强大的私信系统和视频通话
Comment: 0,0:05:14.26,0:05:17.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,推特还与 Etoro 合作   让用户能在推特上炒股
Comment: 0,0:05:18.04,0:05:21.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但我认为最专制的一项改变
Comment: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:26.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,是围绕着访问推特的 API 展开的
Comment: 0,0:05:26.45,0:05:27.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,你可能不知道什么是 API
Comment: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:30.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它指的是“应用程序编程接口”
Comment: 0,0:05:30.90,0:05:35.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它是在不同程序之间交流的协议
Comment: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:39.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,如果你要把数据从一个系统推送到另一个系统
Comment: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,比如从谷歌表单或 Salesforce 到 Stripe
Comment: 0,0:05:42.78,0:05:44.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,你就要用到 API
Comment: 0,0:05:44.64,0:05:46.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,API 在互联网上无处不在
Comment: 0,0:05:47.18,0:05:49.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,对于消费者级在线服务
Comment: 0,0:05:49.05,0:05:52.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,很少有人将 API 拿来收费   要交钱才能用
Comment: 0,0:05:53.16,0:05:55.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,社交媒体尤其如此
Comment: 0,0:05:55.77,0:05:58.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但今年二月   推特就这么做了
Comment: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,开发者和研究人员惊讶地发现
Comment: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们必须付费才能访问推特 API
Comment: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:08.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,成千上万的账户宣布   因为这一变化它们不得不下线
Comment: 0,0:06:08.62,0:06:11.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,从发送天气更新的国家气象局
Comment: 0,0:06:11.31,0:06:14.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,到发送交通更新的地方交通部门
Comment: 0,0:06:14.90,0:06:16.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,当然   还有摸鱼用的段子账户
Comment: 0,0:06:17.48,0:06:20.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,马斯克解释这是为了控制垃圾机器人
Comment: 0,0:06:20.12,0:06:21.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但开发者辩称
Comment: 0,0:06:21.89,0:06:25.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,真正的垃圾机器人来自注入推特   冒充其网页客户端的脚本
Comment: 0,0:06:25.56,0:06:27.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或来自被窃取的 API 秘钥
Comment: 0,0:06:27.68,0:06:31.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,推特有所让步   原来的一些 API 计划被收回了
Comment: 0,0:06:31.48,0:06:35.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,比如重新引入了一个免费额度   尽管是一个极其有限的额度
Comment: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:39.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,然而   他们取消了对第三方客户端的 API 访问
Comment: 0,0:06:39.59,0:06:44.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这也是一个明确的信号   即推特的未来将对其开发者社区越来越不友好
Comment: 0,0:06:45.29,0:06:48.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它想成为互联网的围墙花园
Comment: 0,0:06:48.73,0:06:50.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,另外   我发现一件极其可笑的事
Comment: 0,0:06:51.09,0:06:54.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,要请求访问企业级推特 API
Comment: 0,0:06:54.62,0:06:56.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,你得先填一个谷歌表单
Comment: 0,0:06:56.42,0:06:57.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,推特居然让你填谷歌的表单
Comment: 0,0:06:57.61,0:07:02.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它们就拿谷歌表单来招待一年要交四万二千刀的客户
Comment: 0,0:07:02.89,0:07:03.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,属实难蚌
Comment: 0,0:07:04.32,0:07:06.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在这一变化之后   我们看到红迪也在跟进
Comment: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:09.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,红迪也将开始对其 API 访问收费
Comment: 0,0:07:10.13,0:07:13.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,让开发第三方红迪客户端的开发者望而却步
Comment: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:17.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,甚至是那些提供工具帮助社区管理论坛、调节社区的开发者
Comment: 0,0:07:17.99,0:07:20.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而红迪完全没有提供这些工具
Comment: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:23.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,红迪给出了两方面解释
Comment: 0,0:07:23.26,0:07:26.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,首先   必须承认红迪上有很多有用的
Comment: 0,0:07:26.33,0:07:28.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,且容易得到的信息
Comment: 0,0:07:28.73,0:07:31.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,想想你有多少次在谷歌搜东西时
Comment: 0,0:07:31.71,0:07:33.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在查询内容的末尾加上一个“reddit”
Comment: 0,0:07:34.18,0:07:36.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,关于这一点   我们稍后会详细讨论
Comment: 0,0:07:36.98,0:07:40.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,因此   红迪希望保护自己不受数据搜刮的影响
Comment: 0,0:07:41.06,0:07:43.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,OpenAI 承认红迪确实是
Comment: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:46.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,用来训练其人工智能模型的数据来源之一
Comment: 0,0:07:46.41,0:07:49.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,红迪不希望这种事在它没得一点分成的情况下再次发生
Comment: 0,0:07:50.36,0:07:53.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,另外   随着红迪向上市努力
Comment: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:56.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它想找到新的方法使自己盈利
Comment: 0,0:07:57.30,0:07:59.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但如果不明显的话
Comment: 0,0:07:59.09,0:08:03.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,所有这些事不仅对开发者讲变得更糟   对用户也是如此
Comment: 0,0:08:03.39,0:08:04.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它限制了在这些网站上可以做的事情
Comment: 0,0:08:04.97,0:08:09.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,并推进了这样一种想法   即可以而且应该只有一种方式
Comment: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:12.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,一套被批准的渠道让用户与网站互动
Comment: 0,0:08:13.42,0:08:18.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它消除了提供良好信息的自动账户   使这些网站变得不再有用
Comment: 0,0:08:18.84,0:08:22.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它限制了你能得到的关于你自己和其他人的互联网存在的数据
Comment: 0,0:08:23.17,0:08:26.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它限制了可以在这些网站和社区上进行的研究
Comment: 0,0:08:27.22,0:08:30.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它还通过限制开发者创造不同的和独特的用户体验
Comment: 0,0:08:30.56,0:08:33.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,完全限制了人类的创造力
Comment: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:41.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,今年五月
Comment: 0,0:08:41.51,0:08:45.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,谷歌宣布它会大量删除不活跃的谷歌账户
Comment: 0,0:08:45.48,0:08:49.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,具体的说   两年都没有任何活动的账户
Comment: 0,0:08:49.68,0:08:52.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,无数的邮件及其附件、谷歌云盘的文件、照片   还有其他的
Comment: 0,0:08:53.08,0:08:56.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,都将在今年年底被删除
Comment: 0,0:08:56.61,0:09:00.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,最让我震惊的是   他们发布这一变化的方式相当糟糕
Comment: 0,0:09:00.83,0:09:03.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,就随便放在了安全博客文章中
Comment: 0,0:09:03.90,0:09:07.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,细节的缺失也让人们怀疑
Comment: 0,0:09:07.67,0:09:12.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,如果油管频道关联的谷歌账户不活跃了   整个频道是不是都要删掉
Comment: 0,0:09:12.44,0:09:16.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们在这一反响后才更新博文
Comment: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:19.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,表明他们在第一轮时确实没有关心到这一点
Comment: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:22.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或者说他们一开始确实打算删除油管视频
Comment: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:27.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但是   天啊   即使他们澄清了这些变化   事情仍然很糟糕
Comment: 0,0:09:28.20,0:09:30.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,想想你有一个去世的家庭成员
Comment: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:32.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在永久删除之前   你不知道如何恢复他们的账户
Comment: 0,0:09:33.31,0:09:37.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,亦或是你处于昏迷当中   又或许你进了监狱
Comment: 0,0:09:37.70,0:09:42.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,想象你的谷歌账号   你在线身份的关键   在一瞬间被擦除了
Comment: 0,0:09:42.77,0:09:44.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,哦豁   永远没了
Comment: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:47.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,你得从头开始打一场硬仗
Comment: 0,0:09:47.94,0:09:50.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,证明你是你所说的人
Comment: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:53.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,推特也宣布他们要做同样的事情
Comment: 0,0:09:53.20,0:09:55.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们也要清除不活跃的账号
Comment: 0,0:09:55.94,0:09:59.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,谷歌至少有点礼貌   说这是出于安全原因
Comment: 0,0:09:59.64,0:10:03.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,推特只是想尽可能的减少累赘
Comment: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:07.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们的官方政策规定   如果一个账户在一个月内没有活动
Comment: 0,0:10:07.40,0:10:10.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,就有被删除的风险
Comment: 0,0:10:11.07,0:10:13.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,Imgur 最近也决定
Comment: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:16.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,一堆旧照片和论坛内容不值得再保留了
Comment: 0,0:10:17.09,0:10:21.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这些不成熟的决定本来在社交平台上流行   现在蔓延开来了
Comment: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:26.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,流媒体服务   诸如 Disney+、HBO Max（现在称作 Max）
Comment: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:31.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,Hulu 和 Showtime 取消了对数十部电影和电视节目的访问权限有一段时日了
Comment: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:34.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而且这不仅仅是他们从其他公司授权的内容
Comment: 0,0:10:34.87,0:10:37.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它还包括内部制作的电影和节目
Comment: 0,0:10:38.24,0:10:41.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,通过将他们的影视库限制在时下流行或饱受欢迎的内容上
Comment: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:45.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这些公司在某些情况下可以利用一些税收减免
Comment: 0,0:10:45.96,0:10:51.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或者砍掉他们支付给内容创作者的许可费或剩余费用
Comment: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:54.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在第一季结束后还不到半年
Comment: 0,0:10:55.15,0:10:58.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,Disney+ 的幻想系列剧《风云际会》从流媒体下架了
Comment: 0,0:10:58.80,0:11:00.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,太疯狂了
Comment: 0,0:11:00.08,0:11:02.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,确实   人人都在骂剧本
Comment: 0,0:11:02.61,0:11:05.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但看到一件人们花了多年时间创作的艺术品
Comment: 0,0:11:06.22,0:11:09.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,却被当作什么都没有一样扔掉
Comment: 0,0:11:09.49,0:11:11.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,真是令人难以置信的残忍
Comment: 0,0:11:12.03,0:11:16.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,与此同时   作家罢工正在你看不到的地方进行   这是雪上加霜
Comment: 0,0:11:16.62,0:11:18.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这也意味着   许多情况下
Comment: 0,0:11:18.46,0:11:21.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,不再有合法的手段来观看这些内容
Comment: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:25.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这些网站是自愿删除内容
Comment: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:28.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,其他一些组织就是被迫的了
Comment: 0,0:11:28.80,0:11:30.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,互联网的另一个支柱   互联网档案馆
Comment: 0,0:11:30.89,0:11:33.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,早在三月份的诉讼中受到了重大打击
Comment: 0,0:11:33.54,0:11:36.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,图书出版商认为   互联网档案馆借出数字图书没有法律依据
Comment: 0,0:11:36.99,0:11:40.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,即使是通过有控制的数字借阅也一样
Comment: 0,0:11:40.44,0:11:41.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,法院同意了
Comment: 0,0:11:42.09,0:11:43.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,尽管互联网档案馆正在上诉
Comment: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:51.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但想到如此丰富的知识可能会变得完全无用   仍然是如此悲惨
Comment: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:52.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我不是律师
Comment: 0,0:11:52.69,0:11:55.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,所以我不能以任何权威的方式谈论案件的细节
Comment: 0,0:11:55.66,0:12:00.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但你看   如果可能的话   出版商简直会把实体图书馆都取缔
Comment: 0,0:12:00.75,0:12:04.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,自由和开放地获取信息是互联网精神的核心
Comment: 0,0:12:04.73,0:12:09.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,看到如此多的信息付之一炬   我感到很悲伤
Comment: 0,0:12:09.77,0:12:12.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,公司们只看到那些能赚钱的数据的价值
Comment: 0,0:12:12.58,0:12:17.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,所以这些账户及其相关数据才被他们指定为“数字访问”
Comment: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:21.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,若要说点什么   主流网络平台的这些行动
Comment: 0,0:12:21.64,0:12:23.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,凸显了我们数字体验的脆弱性
Comment: 0,0:12:24.25,0:12:27.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,并提醒我们一个不幸的事实
Comment: 0,0:12:27.98,0:12:31.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我们每天创建和消费的信息如此无常
Comment: 0,0:12:37.48,0:12:40.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,现在在线搜索的状态非常令人作呕
Comment: 0,0:12:41.27,0:12:43.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,如果你天真地在谷歌中输入了一些东西
Comment: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:45.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,谷歌就会用它认为你想要的大量推广
Comment: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:48.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,轮播广告和小部件来轰炸你
Comment: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:51.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,然后   一旦你进入正常的搜索结果
Comment: 0,0:12:51.55,0:12:54.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它就会充斥着一般的聊以安慰的东西
Comment: 0,0:12:54.45,0:12:57.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,以及堆砌关键词的结果列表
Comment: 0,0:12:57.45,0:12:59.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,坦率地说   这些列表往往不会回答你的问题
Comment: 0,0:12:59.65,0:13:02.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在在线搜索领域   管理的负担已经转移到用户身上
Comment: 0,0:13:02.79,0:13:06.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这是一个相当大的发展
Comment: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:10.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这都是由于搜索引擎优化（SEO）的普遍存在
Comment: 0,0:13:10.36,0:13:13.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,也就是以吸引搜索引擎爬虫和算法的方式
Comment: 0,0:13:13.89,0:13:16.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,来格式化和编写网络内容的过程
Comment: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:19.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,然而   SEO 并不像听起来那么简单
Comment: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:24.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,实际上   搜索引擎优化作为一个不断变化的门道
Comment: 0,0:13:24.60,0:13:28.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,对谷歌算法非常依赖   但它的披露既缓慢又模棱两可
Comment: 0,0:13:29.16,0:13:31.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,并需要大量的试错
Comment: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:35.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,正如你可能已经猜到的那样
Comment: 0,0:13:35.38,0:13:37.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这一领域充满了无所不知的“大师”和大量的“万金油”
Comment: 0,0:13:37.43,0:13:42.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我并不是唯一一个蔑视 SEO 的应用如何冲销和同质化互联网的人
Comment: 0,0:13:42.84,0:13:45.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,然而   在许多方面   它是谷歌自己制造的怪物
Comment: 0,0:13:45.99,0:13:47.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,正如一位记者所说
Comment: 0,0:13:47.19,0:13:49.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,谷歌一直在玩一场没完没了的“打鼹鼠”游戏
Comment: 0,0:13:49.77,0:13:53.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,试图通过给他们的网站提供权威内容的所有伪装
Comment: 0,0:13:53.37,0:13:57.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,来打击 SEO 营销人员滥用谷歌的算法   为自己谋取利益
Comment: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:02.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,自然   流量越大   你就越可以加广告来赚钱
Comment: 0,0:14:02.31,0:14:05.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或吸引用户使用你的产品或服务
Comment: 0,0:14:06.11,0:14:08.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而且即使是有有用内容的网站
Comment: 0,0:14:08.04,0:14:11.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,你有时也要浏览一整篇页面来寻找你要的东西
Comment: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:15.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,因为许多网站迎合的是谷歌搜索算法
Comment: 0,0:14:15.39,0:14:18.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而非试图寻找答案的终端用户
Comment: 0,0:14:19.14,0:14:20.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这往往很糟糕
Comment: 0,0:14:20.48,0:14:22.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,正如我之前所说   更多的时候
Comment: 0,0:14:22.42,0:14:26.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,你更可能通过在搜索内容上加一个“reddit”
Comment: 0,0:14:26.77,0:14:28.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在红迪之类的论坛中挖掘   来找到你要的东西
Comment: 0,0:14:28.67,0:14:32.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,作为替代   很多年轻人开始用抖音作为搜索引擎
Comment: 0,0:14:33.13,0:14:36.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,那样可以寻找更真实的、更个性的信息来源
Comment: 0,0:14:36.79,0:14:40.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,连谷歌自己也承认   40% 的 Z 世代
Comment: 0,0:14:40.28,0:14:44.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,选择抖音或者照片墙来搜寻某些东西   而非谷歌
Comment: 0,0:14:44.84,0:14:47.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这不仅仅是结果更没用的事
Comment: 0,0:14:47.39,0:14:50.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这对互联网的历史有着危险的影响
Comment: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:52.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,为了追求托管“常青内容”
Comment: 0,0:14:52.81,0:14:55.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,也就是能够可靠地长期吸引受众的内容
Comment: 0,0:14:55.86,0:14:58.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,文章和博文不断被重写
Comment: 0,0:14:59.07,0:15:02.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,新的超链接   更好的标题   更好的文案
Comment: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:06.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这样做都是为了使内容更有市场   并推动用户继续使用它
Comment: 0,0:15:07.09,0:15:12.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,然而   在几乎没有披露的情况下   历史被改写是一件可悲的事情
Comment: 0,0:15:12.31,0:15:17.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,网络出版商也经常删减他们网站上过时的或不流行的内容
Comment: 0,0:15:17.83,0:15:20.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,正如另一位作家所说
Comment: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:23.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这一切导致了一个没有集体记忆和问责制度的互联网
Comment: 0,0:15:23.88,0:15:25.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,因此当谷歌与必应宣布
Comment: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:29.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,生成性人工智能响应将在未来的搜索中占据中心位置时
Comment: 0,0:15:29.53,0:15:32.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,一些人欢呼这是一个令人难以置信的发展
Comment: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:36.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,希望这将真正给用户提供他们正在寻找的答案
Comment: 0,0:15:36.79,0:15:41.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,其他人则认为   生成式人工智能昭示着 SEO 的死亡
Comment: 0,0:15:41.32,0:15:43.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,生成式人工智能会扼杀很大一部分的有机搜索流量
Comment: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:47.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,尽管它们自己也要引用这些信息
Comment: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:51.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,目前来看   搜索中的生成性人工智能响应似乎很糟糕
Comment: 0,0:15:52.47,0:15:56.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,造成的问题比它解决的要多
Comment: 0,0:15:56.86,0:15:59.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,有些响应分明就是抄来的
Comment: 0,0:15:59.80,0:16:02.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而那些没有发挥作用的部分也往往是错误的
Comment: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:06.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,因为它只是将它认为可能彼此相邻出现的单词串在一起
Comment: 0,0:16:07.01,0:16:10.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,为了让它提供人们所期望的高质量的用户体验
Comment: 0,0:16:10.64,0:16:13.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,有时直接抄也不失为一种好方法
Comment: 0,0:16:13.91,0:16:15.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但这样做的代价是
Comment: 0,0:16:15.10,0:16:18.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,直接侵害了那些提供信息的人
Comment: 0,0:16:19.11,0:16:23.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,另外   既然它抓取的网站都是给搜索引擎优化的
Comment: 0,0:16:24.14,0:16:26.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我想我们会大量遇到一种情况
Comment: 0,0:16:26.60,0:16:28.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,即   喂给它垃圾   吐出来也是垃圾
Comment: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:31.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,一定会有连用户自己
Comment: 0,0:16:31.32,0:16:33.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,也无法找到他们寻找的信息的情况
Comment: 0,0:16:33.80,0:16:36.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而且谷歌与必应的语言模型
Comment: 0,0:16:36.66,0:16:40.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,所参考的页面   和人类用户浏览的页面是完全一样的
Comment: 0,0:16:40.77,0:16:44.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,所以我真的怀疑这些生成式机器人
Comment: 0,0:16:44.28,0:16:46.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,能否做人类用户也做不到的事
Comment: 0,0:16:46.70,0:16:47.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,更糟糕的是
Comment: 0,0:16:48.17,0:16:51.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,谷歌和必应都表明
Comment: 0,0:16:51.03,0:16:52.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们要在人工智能生成的结果中投放广告
Comment: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:56.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,意味着哪怕生成的回复有用
Comment: 0,0:16:57.17,0:16:58.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,也会充满广告
Comment: 0,0:16:58.47,0:17:00.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,让用户体验变得十分乏味
Comment: 0,0:17:00.99,0:17:05.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,谷歌与必应在用户与他们寻找的信息之间塞满垃圾
Comment: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:11.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而且本质上在惩罚拥有优质内容的网站   理由就是优质内容本身
Comment: 0,0:17:11.49,0:17:12.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在我看来
Comment: 0,0:17:12.48,0:17:14.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,当这些模型有优质的信息输入时
Comment: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:16.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它们的确能做许多令人惊叹的事
Comment: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:20.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但这并非互联网现在存在的方式
Comment: 0,0:17:20.87,0:17:24.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,也许这是一个随着时间推移可以解决的技术问题
Comment: 0,0:17:24.40,0:17:27.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但尽管如此   科技公司急不可耐地将尚待完善的东西推向大众
Comment: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:30.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,并对其能力作出巨大的承诺
Comment: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:33.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这仍然是相当可耻和居高临下的
Comment: 0,0:17:33.71,0:17:35.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在搜索引擎刚出现的时候
Comment: 0,0:17:35.98,0:17:37.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它们解决了一个非常具体的问题
Comment: 0,0:17:38.15,0:17:41.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,使互联网的所有角落都能在一个地方找到
Comment: 0,0:17:41.48,0:17:45.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但今天   人们感觉大多数搜索引擎已经放弃了这个承诺
Comment: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:47.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,以用户为中心
Comment: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:50.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,尽管谷歌正在采取措施
Comment: 0,0:17:51.01,0:17:53.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,来提供能将用户与现实世界经验连接的搜索结果
Comment: 0,0:17:53.60,0:17:58.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,让用户能直达此类内容显然已经不是谷歌的第一考虑了
Comment: 0,0:17:59.18,0:18:01.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,只有通过对用户赋能的承诺
Comment: 0,0:18:01.60,0:18:04.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我们才能希望在一个由算法和人工智能主导的时代
Comment: 0,0:18:05.22,0:18:08.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,恢复在线搜索的价值和效用
Comment: 0,0:18:12.71,0:18:15.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,最近   一些油管用户收到通知
Comment: 0,0:18:15.91,0:18:18.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,要求他们停用广告屏蔽器来继续访问油管
Comment: 0,0:18:18.79,0:18:21.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或者说开通油管会员
Comment: 0,0:18:21.59,0:18:24.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我有点惊讶   他们之前也没这么干
Comment: 0,0:18:24.84,0:18:28.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,然而   我们再一次遇到了用户体验大打折扣的十字路口
Comment: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:34.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但说实话   还有一套更隐蔽、更有潜在危害的变化正在发生
Comment: 0,0:18:34.52,0:18:37.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而我还没有听到太多人讨论
Comment: 0,0:18:37.43,0:18:42.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,就是 Chrome 向 Manifest V3 拓展平台迁移
Comment: 0,0:18:42.24,0:18:45.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,清单文件是 Chrome 拓展中许多必需文件中的一个
Comment: 0,0:18:45.94,0:18:49.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它定义了拓展能访问浏览器数据与系统资源的层级
Comment: 0,0:18:49.77,0:18:52.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,拓展的清单文件和它的实际逻辑都是必需的
Comment: 0,0:18:52.60,0:18:57.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,早在 2018 年   谷歌就宣布了他们要过渡到 Manifest V3
Comment: 0,0:18:57.35,0:18:59.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,以替代 Manifest V2
Comment: 0,0:18:59.51,0:19:03.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,尽管迁移时间一拖再拖
Comment: 0,0:19:03.60,0:19:07.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,新规范将带来一些严重的后果
Comment: 0,0:19:08.26,0:19:12.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,第一件大事就是它会破坏去广告插件的有效性
Comment: 0,0:19:12.51,0:19:15.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,以及匿名化插件的能力
Comment: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:19.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,虽然谷歌宣称对清单的这些改变是为了保护隐私
Comment: 0,0:19:20.27,0:19:22.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,对这点   许多开发者表示异议
Comment: 0,0:19:22.47,0:19:27.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它也容易会让网站显示更多广告
Comment: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:30.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,而这正是谷歌整个商业模式的基础
Comment: 0,0:19:30.98,0:19:34.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,最吓人的部分是   这个影响并不限于 Chrome
Comment: 0,0:19:34.36,0:19:38.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它影响的是所有 Chromium 内核的浏览器   如 Edge、Brave、Opera
Comment: 0,0:19:38.93,0:19:43.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,值得注意的唯一一个反对这些更改的浏览器是火狐
Comment: 0,0:19:43.96,0:19:48.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它表示将继续支持 Manifest V2 的网络请求阻止功能
Comment: 0,0:19:48.67,0:19:52.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这是反跟踪扩展和广告屏蔽器的基础
Comment: 0,0:19:52.46,0:19:56.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但当一家公司基本上成为访问互联网的守门人时
Comment: 0,0:19:56.59,0:19:57.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我们就会得到这种结果
Comment: 0,0:19:58.09,0:19:59.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,一旦他们拥有这种权力
Comment: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:02.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们将其用于自己的利益只是时间问题
Comment: 0,0:20:06.09,0:20:08.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,正如我在视频开头所说
Comment: 0,0:20:08.65,0:20:12.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,很多未来主义者在后来变成了法西斯
Comment: 0,0:20:12.42,0:20:14.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,然而   这并非一个逃不开的普遍规则
Comment: 0,0:20:14.96,0:20:18.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,未来主义在各个政治派别都找到了归宿
Comment: 0,0:20:19.24,0:20:24.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,因为   尽管《未来主义宣言》的一些条条款款的反动的
Comment: 0,0:20:24.71,0:20:27.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,未来主义的内核却不是
Comment: 0,0:20:27.77,0:20:31.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我认为未来主义运动值得高度赞扬的一件事是
Comment: 0,0:20:31.38,0:20:35.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,它将一种新发现的对未来的乐观情绪带入了主流
Comment: 0,0:20:36.01,0:20:39.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们赞美技术进步   因为他们看到了其中的好处
Comment: 0,0:20:40.43,0:20:43.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们赞美人类的创造力是一股解放的力量
Comment: 0,0:20:44.05,0:20:45.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,然而   100 多年后的今天
Comment: 0,0:20:45.86,0:20:50.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我很难找到那种乐观的感觉   至少在现代互联网方面是这样
Comment: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:53.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,似乎每一条前进的道路上都有路障
Comment: 0,0:20:53.97,0:20:57.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或者   互联网上取得的任何进展都在倒退
Comment: 0,0:20:58.07,0:21:02.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,当企业将增长的责任放在用户的肩上时
Comment: 0,0:21:02.75,0:21:04.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,不会有任何好处
Comment: 0,0:21:04.50,0:21:08.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,不幸的是   最近这种情况愈见愈多
Comment: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:10.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在为这个视频做研究时
Comment: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:15.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我看到了一篇文章   我认为它完美地概括了我们的方向
Comment: 0,0:21:15.68,0:21:18.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我们正在经历有用的互联网的终结
Comment: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:22.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在未来   网络讨论将在各个圈子内闭门进行   变得嘈杂而封闭
Comment: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:26.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,由大型语言模型产生的   仅在风格上与有用信息相似的垃圾
Comment: 0,0:21:26.42,0:21:31.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,逐渐在面向公众的网络上横行
Comment: 0,0:21:31.30,0:21:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,寻找客观的独立产品评论
Comment: 0,0:21:34.46,0:21:37.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,专家技术支持和各种有用的建议
Comment: 0,0:21:37.70,0:21:41.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,现在将类似于人们搜索非法体育节目
Comment: 0,0:21:41.61,0:21:42.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或盗版期刊文章的过程
Comment: 0,0:21:43.41,0:21:47.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,在红迪等地方发布的数十年的真实人类对话
Comment: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:51.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,将沦为无意识机器人和欺骗性营销者的有用的培训材料   而后者最终会取代前者
Comment: 0,0:21:52.30,0:21:55.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,尽管最近红迪版主的下线抗议固然值得敬佩
Comment: 0,0:21:56.08,0:21:59.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这也改变不了一个事实
Comment: 0,0:22:00.26,0:22:02.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,真正捏着网络平台的   不是网民   是红迪这些公司
Comment: 0,0:22:02.88,0:22:07.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,他们是有法律义务为投资者实现利润最大化的企业
Comment: 0,0:22:07.91,0:22:11.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,可以做出任何他们喜欢的改变   而不管我们自己的感受如何
Comment: 0,0:22:12.05,0:22:15.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,但尽管如此   正如我们所知   这将是互联网的终结
Comment: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:20.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,整个网络的人   各种网站上充满激情的人
Comment: 0,0:22:20.75,0:22:23.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,都有崩溃或被侵蚀的风险
Comment: 0,0:22:24.11,0:22:25.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,或者被雪藏在某个阴暗的角落里
Comment: 0,0:22:26.30,0:22:29.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这是一个如此可悲和不可想象的前景
Comment: 0,0:22:29.74,0:22:32.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,应对这些趋势至关重要
Comment: 0,0:22:33.22,0:22:37.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,以确保互联网仍然是一个充满活力和包容性的创新和协作空间
Comment: 0,0:22:38.20,0:22:39.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,通过倡导开放
Comment: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:42.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,支持开发者和独立创作者
Comment: 0,0:22:42.49,0:22:43.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,并要求企业更加透明
Comment: 0,0:22:44.26,0:22:47.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我们有望努力实现一个更加互联和用户友好的互联网
Comment: 0,0:22:48.03,0:22:52.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,这实际上丰富了我们的生活
Comment: 0,0:22:53.26,0:22:54.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,我是 1C2
Comment: 0,0:22:55.08,0:22:55.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,karaoke,感谢收看
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.99,0:00:37.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这些文字引自意大利诗人菲利波·托马索·马里内蒂的 《未来主义宣言》
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.48,0:00:39.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}发表于 1909 年
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.40,0:00:43.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}通过他的作品   他和他的同伙向世界宣布了一个新的运动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.12,0:00:47.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}崇拜工业进步和人类对自然的胜利
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:53.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们认识到世界已经进入了一个前所未有的技术革新的新时代
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.44,0:00:56.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}因此毫不掩饰地宣称
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.10,0:01:01.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}人类应该摆脱过去的传统、品味和道德的束缚
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.12,0:01:03.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}追求未来
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.82,0:01:06.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}对他们来说   进步应该不惜一切代价
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.99,0:01:08.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}哪怕是牺牲人的生命
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.72,0:01:10.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}除了高度评价战争和暴力
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.09,0:01:15.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}意大利的核心未来主义者也是热心的民族主义者
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.39,0:01:19.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们将这场运动视为意大利在世界舞台上重新证明自己的机会
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.99,0:01:22.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而不是充当某种古代的养老院
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.24,0:01:26.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们还讨厌女性   憎恶女权
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.78,0:01:29.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}所以说   许多意大利未来主义者在未来几十年里
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.05,0:01:33.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}变成法西斯主义者   就不足为奇了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.94,0:01:35.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}回到引文
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.74,0:01:38.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}未来主义者不仅仅想让过去像人类一样自然消亡
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.80,0:01:40.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们想要扼杀过去
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.80,0:01:46.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}摧毁博物馆和图书馆是他们宣言的核心原则
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.49,0:01:49.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}虽然正派的未来主义者运动在二三十年代达到了顶峰
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.95,0:01:54.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但你仍然可以发现他们的哲学元素渗透到我们今天的文化中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.71,0:01:59.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}特别是这个核心主题   这种对前人的不顾一切的蔑视
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:02.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它还没有完全消失
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:09.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我看到这个主题一次又一次地出现   坦率地说   这让我很烦恼
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.13,0:02:22.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}不知道是否只有我在这么想   但互联网的最后几年感觉停滞不前
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.81,0:02:24.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}也许是怀旧滤镜加成
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.67,0:02:29.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但我觉得与 2000 年代和 2010 年代相比
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.60,0:02:31.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}当前的互联网环境感觉不那么乐观和令人兴奋
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:35.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}那时   我们看到基于网络的新服务和产品的爆炸性增长
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.58,0:02:38.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}重新定义了整个行业
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.24,0:02:41.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}从管理销售渠道到纳税   再到看电影   无所不包
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:43.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}简直没有天花板
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.19,0:02:46.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但现在市场已经饱和了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:51.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}不同公司之间的竞争战线已经变得越来越稳固
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.76,0:02:55.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}因此   为了追求不断增加的利润
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.77,0:02:58.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}公司转向从终端用户那里榨取更多的钱
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.98,0:03:03.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}当整个行业拼命寻找其下一个“重新定义”的时刻时
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.43,0:03:07.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}许多公司和投资者认为他们在滥用元宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:11.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或将区块链技术融入一切玩意   就那啥毫无理由
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:13.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}反正用什么脏话来形容都一样
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.16,0:03:16.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}有一段时间   科技公司还像没穿衣服的皇帝一样迷失于此
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:20.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但看起来   硅谷梦想的泡沫终于破灭了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:25.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}现在   互联网行业将人工智能视作下一个科技前沿
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.46,0:03:29.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但是   尽管像 ChatGPT 这样的生成式聊天机器人让人影响深刻
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.37,0:03:32.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}人工智能并不是因特网的救星
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.45,0:03:35.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}从很多方面讲   它的新奇反而在分散我们的注意力
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.91,0:03:40.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}让我们忽视一些真正令人担忧的   让互联网变得更糟糕的趋势
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.86,0:03:44.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}本视频没有一个总体论点
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.75,0:03:48.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}主要是一组困扰我的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:52.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它们表明互联网正走向一个远非互联的未来
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.82,0:03:54.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}所有网站都变成有围墙的花园
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.24,0:03:58.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}每个用户的每分每秒都被挤压出来
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:03:59.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}互联网作为一个整体
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}其作用和可用性都降低了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:08.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}噢   推特
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:10.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}来看看推特
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:15.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}自从埃隆·马斯克在十月夺回公司控制权以来   这段旅程真是美妙呵
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.95,0:04:19.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}全是一个接着一个的令人质疑的决定
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.19,0:04:23.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我的稿子不知道改了多少回
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:26.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}都跟不上推特做的屑事情
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:31.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在广告商大量外流后
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.16,0:04:34.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}与去年相比   推特在美广告收入减少了 59%
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:38.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而推特蓝标会员只能从该公司可能损失的数亿美元中
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.26,0:04:42.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}捡回 1100 万美元
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.71,0:04:44.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而且这个数据很可能过时了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.27,0:04:49.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}一项较新的数据显示   最早开通蓝标会员的用户中
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.37,0:04:51.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}一半以上都不再续订它了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:54.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}马斯克明确表示他想要把推特转型
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.74,0:04:57.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}转成“X” 一个全能的超级应用
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.99,0:05:01.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}所有的沟通交流、财务
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.17,0:05:03.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}和媒体消费都在一个应用   如同中国的微信
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.50,0:05:07.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我们已经看到推特全力推进自我转型
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.88,0:05:09.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}推特公司已更名为 X 公司
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.98,0:05:13.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}马斯克宣布   推特会加入更强大的私信系统和视频通话
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.26,0:05:17.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}推特还与 Etoro 合作   让用户能在推特上炒股
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.04,0:05:21.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但我认为最专制的一项改变
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:26.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}是围绕着访问推特的 API 展开的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.45,0:05:27.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}你可能不知道什么是 API
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:30.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它指的是“应用程序编程接口”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.90,0:05:35.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它是在不同程序之间交流的协议
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:39.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}如果你要把数据从一个系统推送到另一个系统
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}比如从谷歌表单或 Salesforce 到 Stripe
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.78,0:05:44.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}你就要用到 API
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.64,0:05:46.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}API 在互联网上无处不在
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.18,0:05:49.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}对于消费者级在线服务
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.05,0:05:52.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}很少有人将 API 拿来收费   要交钱才能用
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.16,0:05:55.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}社交媒体尤其如此
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:05:58.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但今年二月   推特就这么做了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}开发者和研究人员惊讶地发现
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们必须付费才能访问推特 API
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:08.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}成千上万的账户宣布   因为这一变化它们不得不下线
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.62,0:06:11.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}从发送天气更新的国家气象局
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.31,0:06:14.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}到发送交通更新的地方交通部门
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.90,0:06:16.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}当然   还有摸鱼用的段子账户
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.48,0:06:20.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}马斯克解释这是为了控制垃圾机器人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.12,0:06:21.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但开发者辩称
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.89,0:06:25.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}真正的垃圾机器人来自注入推特   冒充其网页客户端的脚本
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.56,0:06:27.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或来自被窃取的 API 秘钥
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.68,0:06:31.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}推特有所让步   原来的一些 API 计划被收回了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.48,0:06:35.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}比如重新引入了一个免费额度   尽管是一个极其有限的额度
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:39.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}然而   他们取消了对第三方客户端的 API 访问
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.59,0:06:44.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这也是一个明确的信号   即推特的未来将对其开发者社区越来越不友好
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.29,0:06:48.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它想成为互联网的围墙花园
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.73,0:06:50.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}另外   我发现一件极其可笑的事
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.09,0:06:54.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}要请求访问企业级推特 API
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.62,0:06:56.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}你得先填一个谷歌表单
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.42,0:06:57.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}推特居然让你填谷歌的表单
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.61,0:07:02.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它们就拿谷歌表单来招待一年要交四万二千刀的客户
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.89,0:07:03.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}属实难蚌
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.32,0:07:06.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在这一变化之后   我们看到红迪也在跟进
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:09.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}红迪也将开始对其 API 访问收费
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.13,0:07:13.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}让开发第三方红迪客户端的开发者望而却步
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:17.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}甚至是那些提供工具帮助社区管理论坛、调节社区的开发者
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.99,0:07:20.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而红迪完全没有提供这些工具
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:23.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}红迪给出了两方面解释
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.26,0:07:26.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}首先   必须承认红迪上有很多有用的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.33,0:07:28.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}且容易得到的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.73,0:07:31.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}想想你有多少次在谷歌搜东西时
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.71,0:07:33.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在查询内容的末尾加上一个“reddit”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.18,0:07:36.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}关于这一点   我们稍后会详细讨论
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.98,0:07:40.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}因此   红迪希望保护自己不受数据搜刮的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.06,0:07:43.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}OpenAI 承认红迪确实是
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:46.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}用来训练其人工智能模型的数据来源之一
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.41,0:07:49.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}红迪不希望这种事在它没得一点分成的情况下再次发生
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.36,0:07:53.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}另外   随着红迪向上市努力
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:56.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它想找到新的方法使自己盈利
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.30,0:07:59.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但如果不明显的话
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.09,0:08:03.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}所有这些事不仅对开发者讲变得更糟   对用户也是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.39,0:08:04.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它限制了在这些网站上可以做的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.97,0:08:09.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}并推进了这样一种想法   即可以而且应该只有一种方式
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:12.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}一套被批准的渠道让用户与网站互动
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.42,0:08:18.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它消除了提供良好信息的自动账户   使这些网站变得不再有用
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.84,0:08:22.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它限制了你能得到的关于你自己和其他人的互联网存在的数据
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.17,0:08:26.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它限制了可以在这些网站和社区上进行的研究
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.22,0:08:30.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它还通过限制开发者创造不同的和独特的用户体验
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.56,0:08:33.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}完全限制了人类的创造力
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:41.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}今年五月
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.51,0:08:45.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}谷歌宣布它会大量删除不活跃的谷歌账户
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.48,0:08:49.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}具体的说   两年都没有任何活动的账户
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.68,0:08:52.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}无数的邮件及其附件、谷歌云盘的文件、照片   还有其他的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.08,0:08:56.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}都将在今年年底被删除
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.61,0:09:00.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}最让我震惊的是   他们发布这一变化的方式相当糟糕
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.83,0:09:03.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}就随便放在了安全博客文章中
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.90,0:09:07.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}细节的缺失也让人们怀疑
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.67,0:09:12.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}如果油管频道关联的谷歌账户不活跃了   整个频道是不是都要删掉
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.44,0:09:16.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们在这一反响后才更新博文
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:19.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}表明他们在第一轮时确实没有关心到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:22.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或者说他们一开始确实打算删除油管视频
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:27.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但是   天啊   即使他们澄清了这些变化   事情仍然很糟糕
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.20,0:09:30.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}想想你有一个去世的家庭成员
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:32.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在永久删除之前   你不知道如何恢复他们的账户
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.31,0:09:37.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}亦或是你处于昏迷当中   又或许你进了监狱
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.70,0:09:42.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}想象你的谷歌账号   你在线身份的关键   在一瞬间被擦除了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.77,0:09:44.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}哦豁   永远没了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:47.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}你得从头开始打一场硬仗
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.94,0:09:50.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}证明你是你所说的人
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:53.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}推特也宣布他们要做同样的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.20,0:09:55.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们也要清除不活跃的账号
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.94,0:09:59.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}谷歌至少有点礼貌   说这是出于安全原因
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.64,0:10:03.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}推特只是想尽可能的减少累赘
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:07.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们的官方政策规定   如果一个账户在一个月内没有活动
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.40,0:10:10.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}就有被删除的风险
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.07,0:10:13.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}Imgur 最近也决定
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:16.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}一堆旧照片和论坛内容不值得再保留了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.09,0:10:21.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}尽管始作俑者是那些论坛   Imgur 的举动首先让社区炸开了锅
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:26.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}流媒体服务   诸如 Disney+、HBO Max（现在称作 Max）
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:31.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}Hulu 和 Showtime 取消了对数十部电影和电视节目的访问权限有一段时日了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:34.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而且这不仅仅是他们从其他公司授权的内容
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.87,0:10:37.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它还包括内部制作的电影和节目
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.24,0:10:41.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}通过将他们的影视库限制在时下流行或饱受欢迎的内容上
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:45.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这些公司在某些情况下可以利用一些税收减免
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.96,0:10:51.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或者砍掉他们支付给内容创作者的许可费或剩余费用
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:54.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在第一季结束后还不到半年
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.15,0:10:58.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}Disney+ 的幻想系列剧《风云际会》从流媒体下架了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.80,0:11:00.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}太疯狂了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.08,0:11:02.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}确实   人人都在骂剧本
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.61,0:11:05.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但看到一件人们花了多年时间创作的艺术品
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.22,0:11:09.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}却被当作什么都没有一样扔掉
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.49,0:11:11.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}真是令人难以置信的残忍
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.03,0:11:16.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}与此同时   作家罢工正在你看不到的地方进行   这是雪上加霜
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.62,0:11:18.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这也意味着   许多情况下
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.46,0:11:21.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}不再有合法的手段来观看这些内容
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:25.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这些网站是自愿删除内容
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:28.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}其他一些组织就是被迫的了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.80,0:11:30.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}互联网的另一个支柱   互联网档案馆
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.89,0:11:33.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}早在三月份的诉讼中受到了重大打击
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.54,0:11:36.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}图书出版商认为   互联网档案馆借出数字图书没有法律依据
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.99,0:11:40.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}即使是通过有控制的数字借阅也一样
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.44,0:11:41.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}法院同意了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.09,0:11:43.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}尽管互联网档案馆正在上诉
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:51.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但想到如此丰富的知识可能会变得完全无用   仍然是如此悲惨
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:52.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我不是律师
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.69,0:11:55.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}所以我不能以任何权威的方式谈论案件的细节
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.66,0:12:00.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但你看   如果可能的话   出版商简直会把实体图书馆都取缔
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.75,0:12:04.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}自由和开放地获取信息是互联网精神的核心
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.73,0:12:09.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}看到如此多的信息付之一炬   我感到很悲伤
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.77,0:12:12.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}公司们只看到那些能赚钱的数据的价值
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.58,0:12:17.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}所以这些账户及其相关数据才被他们指定为“数字访问”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:21.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}若要说点什么   主流网络平台的这些行动
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.64,0:12:23.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}凸显了我们数字体验的脆弱性
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.25,0:12:27.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}并提醒我们一个不幸的事实
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.98,0:12:31.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我们每天创建和消费的信息如此无常
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.48,0:12:40.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}现在在线搜索的状态非常令人作呕
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.27,0:12:43.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}如果你天真地在谷歌中输入了一些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:45.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}谷歌就会用它认为你想要的大量推广
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:48.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}轮播广告和小部件来轰炸你
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:51.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}然后   一旦你进入正常的搜索结果
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.55,0:12:54.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它就会充斥着一般的聊以安慰的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.45,0:12:57.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}以及堆砌关键词的结果列表
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.45,0:12:59.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}坦率地说   这些列表往往不会回答你的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.65,0:13:02.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在在线搜索领域   管理的负担已经转移到用户身上
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.79,0:13:06.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这是一个相当大的发展
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:10.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这都是由于搜索引擎优化（SEO）的普遍存在
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.36,0:13:13.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}也就是以吸引搜索引擎爬虫和算法的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.89,0:13:16.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}来格式化和编写网络内容的过程
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:19.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}然而   SEO 并不像听起来那么简单
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:24.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}实际上   搜索引擎优化作为一个不断变化的门道
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.60,0:13:28.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}对谷歌算法非常依赖   但它的披露既缓慢又模棱两可
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.16,0:13:31.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}并需要大量的试错
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:35.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}正如你可能已经猜到的那样
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.38,0:13:37.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这一领域充满了无所不知的“大师”和大量的“万金油”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.43,0:13:42.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我并不是唯一一个蔑视 SEO 的应用如何冲销和同质化互联网的人
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.84,0:13:45.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}然而   在许多方面   它是谷歌自己制造的怪物
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.99,0:13:47.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}正如一位记者所说
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.19,0:13:49.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}谷歌一直在玩一场没完没了的“打鼹鼠”游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.77,0:13:53.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}试图通过给他们的网站提供权威内容的所有伪装
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.37,0:13:57.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}来打击 SEO 营销人员滥用谷歌的算法   为自己谋取利益
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:02.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}自然   流量越大   你就越可以加广告来赚钱
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.31,0:14:05.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或吸引用户使用你的产品或服务
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.11,0:14:08.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而且即使是有有用内容的网站
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.04,0:14:11.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}你有时也要浏览一整篇页面来寻找你要的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:15.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}因为许多网站迎合的是谷歌搜索算法
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.39,0:14:18.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而非试图寻找答案的终端用户
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.14,0:14:20.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这往往很糟糕
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.48,0:14:22.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}正如我之前所说   更多的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.42,0:14:26.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}你更可能通过在搜索内容上加一个“reddit”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.77,0:14:28.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在红迪之类的论坛中挖掘   来找到你要的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.67,0:14:32.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}作为替代   很多年轻人开始用抖音作为搜索引擎
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.13,0:14:36.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}那样可以寻找更真实的、更个性的信息来源
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.79,0:14:40.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}连谷歌自己也承认   40% 的 Z 世代
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.28,0:14:44.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}选择抖音或者照片墙来搜寻某些东西   而非谷歌
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.84,0:14:47.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这不仅仅是结果更没用的事
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.39,0:14:50.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这对互联网的历史有着危险的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:52.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}为了追求托管“常青内容”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.81,0:14:55.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}也就是能够可靠地长期吸引受众的内容
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.86,0:14:58.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}文章和博文不断被重写
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.07,0:15:02.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}新的超链接   更好的标题   更好的文案
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:06.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这样做都是为了使内容更有市场   并推动用户继续使用它
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.09,0:15:12.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}然而   在几乎没有披露的情况下   历史被改写是一件可悲的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.31,0:15:17.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}网络出版商也经常删减他们网站上过时的或不流行的内容
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.83,0:15:20.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}正如另一位作家所说
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:23.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这一切导致了一个没有集体记忆和问责制度的互联网
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.88,0:15:25.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}因此当谷歌与必应宣布
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:29.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}生成性人工智能响应将在未来的搜索中占据中心位置时
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.53,0:15:32.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}一些人欢呼这是一个令人难以置信的发展
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:36.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}希望这将真正给用户提供他们正在寻找的答案
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.79,0:15:41.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}其他人则认为   生成式人工智能昭示着 SEO 的死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.32,0:15:43.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}生成式人工智能会扼杀很大一部分的有机搜索流量
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:47.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}尽管它们自己也要引用这些信息
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:51.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}目前来看   搜索中的生成性人工智能响应似乎很糟糕
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.47,0:15:56.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}造成的问题比它解决的要多
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.86,0:15:59.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}有些响应分明就是抄来的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.80,0:16:02.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而那些没有发挥作用的部分也往往是错误的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:06.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}因为它只是将它认为可能彼此相邻出现的单词串在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.01,0:16:10.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}为了让它提供人们所期望的高质量的用户体验
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.64,0:16:13.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}有时直接抄也不失为一种好方法
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.91,0:16:15.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但这样做的代价是
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.10,0:16:18.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}直接侵害了那些提供信息的人
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.11,0:16:23.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}另外   既然它抓取的网站都是给搜索引擎优化的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.14,0:16:26.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我想我们会大量遇到一种情况
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.60,0:16:28.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}即   喂给它垃圾   吐出来也是垃圾
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:31.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}一定会有连用户自己
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.32,0:16:33.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}也无法找到他们寻找的信息的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.80,0:16:36.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而且谷歌与必应的语言模型
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.66,0:16:40.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}所参考的页面   和人类用户浏览的页面是完全一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.77,0:16:44.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}所以我真的怀疑这些生成式机器人
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.28,0:16:46.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}能否做人类用户也做不到的事
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.70,0:16:47.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}更糟糕的是
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.17,0:16:51.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}谷歌和必应都表明
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.03,0:16:52.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们要在人工智能生成的结果中投放广告
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:56.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}意味着哪怕生成的回复有用
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.17,0:16:58.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}也会充满广告
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.47,0:17:00.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}让用户体验变得十分乏味
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.99,0:17:05.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}谷歌与必应在用户与他们寻找的信息之间塞满垃圾
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:11.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而且本质上在惩罚拥有优质内容的网站   理由就是优质内容本身
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.49,0:17:12.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在我看来
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.48,0:17:14.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}当这些模型有优质的信息输入时
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:16.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它们的确能做许多令人惊叹的事
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:20.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但这并非互联网现在存在的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.87,0:17:24.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}也许这是一个随着时间推移可以解决的技术问题
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.40,0:17:27.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但尽管如此   科技公司急不可耐地将尚待完善的东西推向大众
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:30.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}并对其能力作出巨大的承诺
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:33.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这仍然是相当可耻和居高临下的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.71,0:17:35.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在搜索引擎刚出现的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.98,0:17:37.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它们解决了一个非常具体的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.15,0:17:41.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}使互联网的所有角落都能在一个地方找到
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.48,0:17:45.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但今天   人们感觉大多数搜索引擎已经放弃了这个承诺
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:47.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}以用户为中心
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:50.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}尽管谷歌正在采取措施
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.01,0:17:53.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}来提供能将用户与现实世界经验连接的搜索结果
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.60,0:17:58.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}让用户能直达此类内容显然已经不是谷歌的第一考虑了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.18,0:18:01.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}只有通过对用户赋能的承诺
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.60,0:18:04.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我们才能希望在一个由算法和人工智能主导的时代
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.22,0:18:08.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}恢复在线搜索的价值和效用
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.71,0:18:15.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}最近   一些油管用户收到通知
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.91,0:18:18.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}要求他们停用广告屏蔽器来继续访问油管
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.79,0:18:21.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或者说开通油管会员
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.59,0:18:24.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我有点惊讶   他们之前也没这么干
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.84,0:18:28.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}然而   我们再一次遇到了用户体验大打折扣的十字路口
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:34.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但说实话   还有一套更隐蔽、更有潜在危害的变化正在发生
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.52,0:18:37.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而我还没有听到太多人讨论
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.43,0:18:42.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}就是 Chrome 向 Manifest V3 拓展平台迁移
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.24,0:18:45.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}清单文件是 Chrome 拓展中许多必需文件中的一个
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.94,0:18:49.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它定义了拓展能访问浏览器数据与系统资源的层级
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.77,0:18:52.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}拓展的清单文件和它的实际逻辑都是必需的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.60,0:18:57.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}早在 2018 年   谷歌就宣布了他们要过渡到 Manifest V3
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.35,0:18:59.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}以替代 Manifest V2
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.51,0:19:03.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}尽管迁移时间一拖再拖
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.60,0:19:07.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}新规范将带来一些严重的后果
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.26,0:19:12.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}第一件大事就是它会破坏去广告插件的有效性
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.51,0:19:15.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}以及匿名化插件的能力
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:19.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}虽然谷歌宣称对清单的这些改变是为了保护隐私
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.27,0:19:22.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}对这点   许多开发者表示异议
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.47,0:19:27.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它也容易会让网站显示更多广告
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:30.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}而这正是谷歌整个商业模式的基础
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.98,0:19:34.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}最吓人的部分是   这个影响并不限于 Chrome
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.36,0:19:38.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它影响的是所有 Chromium 内核的浏览器   如 Edge、Brave、Opera
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.93,0:19:43.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}值得注意的唯一一个反对这些更改的浏览器是火狐
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.96,0:19:48.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它表示将继续支持 Manifest V2 的网络请求阻止功能
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.67,0:19:52.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这是反跟踪扩展和广告屏蔽器的基础
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.46,0:19:56.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但当一家公司基本上成为访问互联网的守门人时
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:19:57.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我们就会得到这种结果
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:19:59.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}一旦他们拥有这种权力
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:02.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们将其用于自己的利益只是时间问题
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.09,0:20:08.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}正如我在视频开头所说
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.65,0:20:12.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}很多未来主义者在后来变成了法西斯
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.42,0:20:14.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}然而   这并非一个逃不开的普遍规则
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.96,0:20:18.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}未来主义在各个政治派别都找到了归宿
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.24,0:20:24.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}因为   尽管《未来主义宣言》的一些条款是反动的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.71,0:20:27.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}未来主义的内核却不是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.77,0:20:31.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我认为未来主义运动值得高度赞扬的一件事是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.38,0:20:35.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}它将一种新发现的对未来的乐观情绪带入了主流
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.01,0:20:39.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们赞美技术进步   因为他们看到了其中的好处
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.43,0:20:43.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们赞美人类的创造力是一股解放的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.05,0:20:45.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}然而   100 多年后的今天
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.86,0:20:50.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我很难找到那种乐观的感觉   至少在现代互联网方面是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:53.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}似乎每一条前进的道路上都有路障
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.97,0:20:57.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或者   互联网上取得的任何进展都在倒退
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.07,0:21:02.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}当企业将增长的责任放在用户的肩上时
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.75,0:21:04.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}不会有任何好处
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.50,0:21:08.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}不幸的是   最近这种情况愈见愈多
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:10.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在为这个视频做研究时
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:15.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我看到了一篇文章   我认为它完美地概括了我们的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.68,0:21:18.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我们正在经历有用的互联网的终结
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:22.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在未来   网络讨论将在各个圈子内闭门进行   变得嘈杂而封闭
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:26.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}由大型语言模型产生的   仅在风格上与有用信息相似的垃圾
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.42,0:21:31.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}逐渐在面向公众的网络上横行
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.30,0:21:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}寻找客观的独立产品评论
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.46,0:21:37.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}专家技术支持和各种有用的建议
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.70,0:21:41.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}现在将类似于人们搜索非法体育节目
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.61,0:21:42.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或盗版期刊文章的过程
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.41,0:21:47.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}在红迪等地方发布的数十年的真实人类对话
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:51.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}将沦为无意识机器人和欺骗性营销者的有用的培训材料   而后者最终会取代前者
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.30,0:21:55.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}尽管最近红迪版主的下线抗议固然值得敬佩
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.08,0:21:59.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这也改变不了一个事实
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.26,0:22:02.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}真正捏着网络平台的   不是网民   是红迪这些公司
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.88,0:22:07.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}他们是有法律义务为投资者实现利润最大化的企业
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.91,0:22:11.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}可以做出任何他们喜欢的改变   而不管我们自己的感受如何
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.05,0:22:15.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}但尽管如此   正如我们所知   这将是互联网的终结
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:20.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}整个网络的人   各种网站上充满激情的人
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.75,0:22:23.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}都有崩溃或被侵蚀的风险
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.11,0:22:25.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}或者被雪藏在某个阴暗的角落里
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.30,0:22:29.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这是一个如此可悲和不可想象的前景
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.74,0:22:32.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}应对这些趋势至关重要
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.22,0:22:37.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}以确保互联网仍然是一个充满活力和包容性的创新和协作空间
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.20,0:22:39.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}通过倡导开放
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:42.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}支持开发者和独立创作者
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.49,0:22:43.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}并要求企业更加透明
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.26,0:22:47.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我们有望努力实现一个更加互联和用户友好的互联网
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.03,0:22:52.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}这实际上丰富了我们的生活
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.26,0:22:54.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}我是 1C2
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.08,0:22:55.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,fx,{\pos(960,1032)}感谢收看
